ACQUISITION: N.V. Philips's Polygram Records bought A&M Records, as expected.
No price was given, but an industry official estimated the value at $500 million.
Jerry Moss and Gil Friesen, A&M's chairman and president, respectively, will keep their roles.
The sale includes all of A&M's record operations, its music video interests and A&M's Los Angeles offices but not the music-publishing interests. 

HOCKEY: Coca-Cola Co. signed a multi-year marketing agreement with the National Hockey League.
Terms weren't disclosed.
Coke gets to use the names, symbols, emblems and logos of the NHL and its 21-member clubs in the U.S. and Canada.
Also, Coke agreed to sponsor a youth hockey program in NHL markets as well as a youth hockey camp. 

